other_tests.findings: A retrocecal appendix is dilated to 11 mm with fluid. There is a small amount of fluid in the periappendiceal mesentery with adjacent stranding. No free air is seen.
A large bilobed fibroid is seen arising from the posterior wall of the uterus measuring 9.1 x 9.6 x 6.7 cm (previously 9.0 x 10.4 x 5.6 cm), and a corpus luteum cyst is seen within the right ovary.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The fibroid size decreased slightly from 9.0 x 10.4 x 5.6 cm to 9.1 x 9.6 x 6.7 cm, likely due to partial involution of the necrotic posterior portion.
